task.summary: Add project configuration files and .gitignore for initial Android setup
Add project configuration files and .gitignore for initial Android setup

chore: remove redundant plugins, update dependencies, and add CI workflow
- Removed explicit Kotlin Android and Dokka plugin applications from build scripts - Updated Hilt and Dagger compiler versions in annotationProcessors.json - Added androidx.compose.material.icons.extended and hilt-navigation-compose dependencies - Updated Gradle properties for project naming and lint baseline - Refactored C++/JNI code for formatting and resource management - Added new test stubs for Markdown validation and Gradle version catalog - Updated .ninja_log and build_stdout files for native builds - Added android.yml for GitHub Actions CI - Simplified dependabot.yml configuration - Miscellaneous cleanup and formatting improvements across project files

chore: update to Kotlin 2.3.0, migrate plugin usage, and align JVM/Java targets
- Bump Kotlin version to 2.3.0 and update related dependencies - Replace deprecated plugin aliases with direct plugin application - Switch to org.jetbrains.compose plugin for Compose projects - Standardize JVM toolchain and Java compatibility to version 21/24 across modules - Remove unused plugin aliases from root build script - Update serialization plugin usage to match new Kotlin version - Clean up redundant dependencies and improve build script consistency
